content:
When you load data into a dataset, CRM Analytics tags a text (dimension) column as a number (measure) column if it contains only numbers. For example, CRM Analytics tags a numerical Room Number column as the number type, even though it’s text that identifies rooms.

To group and filter by a number column, use the Number To Text transformation to change a Number column type to Text. You can group and filter by text columns only.

In the Transform node of a Data Prep recipe, select the number (measure) column you want to convert to the Text (dimension) column type.

Select Number to | Text in the Transform toolbar.

Under Show Results In, select whether the new values appear in a new column and whether to keep the original column. Set the label under Column Label if creating a column.

Based on the output column’s datatype, you can set attributes such as API Name, Precision, Scale, Length, and Date Format.

To add the transformation to the Transform node, click Apply. The Preview tab shows the text column. Save the recipe and run it to convert the column type to Text.
title: Data Prep Transformation: Number to Text Conversion
